# DreamStage — FYP Project Specification
# 3D Event Planning & Venue Visualization Platform
# Version 3.0 | 2025

---

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

DreamStage is a web-based 3D event planning and venue visualization platform. It allows event planners and their clients to collaboratively design, customize, and manage events inside pre-built, professionally modelled 3D venue environments — all within a standard web browser, with no specialist software required.

It replaces fragmented tools (spreadsheets, email threads, floor-plan tools, calendar apps) with a single integrated platform.

---

## TECHNOLOGY STACK

- **Frontend:** React.js (with Three.js / React Three Fiber for 3D editor)
- **Backend:** Node.js + Express.js (RESTful API)
- **Database:** PostgreSQL
- **Auth:** JWT (stateless, role-based)
- **Storage:** Private cloud storage bucket (signed URLs for vendor PDFs)
- **3D Engine:** Three.js (scene serialized to JSON for persistence)

---

## FIVE CORE MODULES

### Module A — 3D Venue Editor
- Drag-and-drop asset placement inside pre-built venue templates
- Real-time position, rotation, scale controls
- Auto-save scene every 60 seconds
- Scene serialized as JSON to DB (SceneLayout table)
- Locked after client approval; planner can unlock with confirmation

### Module B — Budget & Cost Estimation Engine
- Budget recalculates within 500ms of any layout change
- Each placed asset triggers a cost update
- Budget ceiling set per event
- Vendor payment tracking (deposit / final)
- Planner can attach vendor quotes (PDF, max 10MB)

### Module C — Client Collaboration & Approval Workflow
- Planner shares read-only project link (UUID v4 token, optional password)
- Client views 3D layout (orbit + walkthrough modes), budget summary, leaves timestamped comments
- Client submits formal approval → triggers layout lock
- Approval stored as immutable audit record (cannot be updated or deleted)
- Project lifecycle state machine: Draft → Approved → Locked

### Module D — Venue Inventory Management
- Venue templates managed by Admin
- Booking conflict check when planner selects venue + date
- Prevents double-booking via DB transactions

### Module E — Décor & Asset Inventory Management
- Stock quantity tracked per asset
- Real-time stock check (<300ms) when asset placed in editor
- Warns planner before overcommitting stock
- Stock reservations per event stored in StockReservation table

### Module F — Multi-Event Project Dashboard (+ Checklist)
- Planner manages multiple concurrent events
- Checklist dynamically populated based on days until event
- Milestones, notes, day-of timeline per event

---

## USER ROLES & PERMISSIONS

### Planner
- Create, manage, delete event projects
- Design 3D layouts, manage budgets, log vendor payments
- Share project link with clients
- View/respond to client comments
- Unlock layout post-approval (with confirmation)

### Client (no registration required)
- Access project via unique shared URL
- View 3D layout (read-only, orbit + walkthrough)
- View budget summary (planner may hide detailed breakdown)
- Leave timestamped comments
- Submit formal design approval

### Admin
- Manage venue template library (add/edit/toggle availability)
- Manage asset/décor inventory (stock, pricing, 3D model refs)
- View and moderate planner accounts
- Monitor venue bookings, resolve conflicts
- Configure system-wide default pricing

---

## DATABASE SCHEMA (Core Tables)

```
User            — id, name, email, password_hash, role, created_at
Event           — id, planner_id, name, type, date, status, share_token, share_password_hash, budget_ceiling
VenueTemplate   — id, name, category, capacity, thumbnail_url, is_active
VenueBooking    — id, event_id, venue_template_id, date, status (provisional / confirmed)
SceneLayout     — id, event_id, scene_json, version, locked, created_at, updated_at
BudgetItem      — id, event_id, asset_id, quantity, unit_price_override, vendor_id
Vendor          — id, event_id, name, company, email, phone, category
VendorPayment   — id, vendor_id, amount, type (deposit / final), paid_at
Asset           — id, name, category, default_unit_price, stock_quantity, model_ref, is_active
StockReservation— id, event_id, asset_id, quantity_reserved
ClientComment   — id, event_id, content, created_at, parent_comment_id
Approval        — id, event_id, client_identifier, approved_at, scene_version_ref
ChecklistItem   — id, event_id, title, due_date, is_complete, is_system_generated
Milestone       — id, event_id, title, target_date, is_complete
TimelineEntry   — id, event_id, time_slot, title, description, sort_order
```

---

## KEY CROSS-MODULE DATA FLOWS

- **3D Editor → Budget:** Every asset placement triggers live budget recalculation
- **3D Editor → Décor Inventory:** Asset placement triggers real-time stock validation
- **Venue Selection → Venue Inventory:** Date selection triggers conflict check
- **Client Approval → Layout Lock:** Approval locks the 3D editor
- **Checklist → Event Date:** Checklist priorities driven by days remaining to event

---

## NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

### Performance
- 3D editor: min 30fps on mid-range laptop (Intel i5, integrated graphics) with up to 100 assets
- Budget recalculation: < 500ms
- Page load: < 3 seconds on ≥10 Mbps connection
- Stock validation: < 300ms

### Security
- Passwords: bcrypt, min cost factor 12; never logged or stored plain-text
- All API routes: JWT + role validation before processing
- Shared links: UUID v4 tokens (no sequential IDs)
- Vendor PDFs: MIME validation, 10MB cap, private bucket with signed URLs
- Protection against SQL injection (parameterized queries) and XSS (output escaping)

### Usability
- 3D editor usable without prior 3D experience (new user places/moves/resizes asset within 5 minutes)
- Client shared view: fully functional on mobile browsers, no app/plugin required
- Human-readable validation messages throughout
- Calendar and stock indicators update without page reload

### Reliability & Data Integrity
- Auto-save scene every 60 seconds
- Venue and stock reservations use DB transactions (prevent race conditions)
- Approval audit trail is immutable (no update/delete by any role)

### Scalability
- Stateless backend (JWT-based sessions) for horizontal scaling
- DB schema supports thousands of concurrent projects with proper indexing on FKs and filtered columns

---

## EXPLICITLY OUT OF SCOPE

- AI-generated 3D models or image-to-3D conversion
- Custom 3D asset uploads by planners (admin-only asset library)
- Payment gateway / financial transactions between users
- Native mobile apps (iOS/Android) — web-only, mobile-responsive
- Real-time collaborative 3D editing by multiple simultaneous users
- Third-party calendar integrations (Google Calendar, Outlook, iCal)
- SMS notifications (in-app and email only)
- White-label / multi-tenant functionality
- Physical vendor marketplace

