## CODING CONVENTIONS & EXPECTATIONS

- Follow RESTful API design — all routes must validate JWT and role before processing
- Use parameterized queries at all times — no raw SQL string interpolation
- All state machine transitions (Draft → Approved → Locked) enforced at API level, not just UI
- Shared project URLs must use UUID v4 — never sequential IDs
- Scene JSON must fully capture Three.js graph (object types, UUIDs, positions, rotations, scales, lighting) for faithful reconstruction
- Use DB transactions for any venue booking or stock reservation operations
- Approval records are write-once — never add update/delete endpoints for the Approval table
- Frontend: use React with React Three Fiber for 3D, keep 3D scene state managed carefully to avoid stale reads on budget/stock sync
